Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] NeoForge Block Drops, Block Break, and Harvest Hooks

Injects NeoForge hooks for block breaking and drops system:
- Block.playerDestroy — handleBlockDrops (BlockDropsEvent, full replacement)
- ServerGamePacketListenerImpl.handlePlayerAction (START_DESTROY_BLOCK) — fireBlockBreak (BreakEvent)
- Player.hasCorrectToolForDrops — doPlayerHarvestCheck (HarvestCheck)
- Player.getDigSpeed — getBreakSpeed (BreakSpeed)
- Player.attack (tool durability) — onPlayerDestroyItem
- ResultSlot.onTake — firePlayerCraftingEvent (PlayerCraftingEvent)
- AbstractFurnaceBlockEntity — firePlayerSmeltedEvent (PlayerSmeltedEvent)
- ServerGamePacketListenerImpl.handleContainerClick — onPlayerBrewedPotion

These hooks allow mods to completely control block breaking, drops,
harvest speed, and the full inventory crafting lifecycle.
diff --git a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/Block.java b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/Block.java
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..1111111111111111111111111111111111111111 100644
--- a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/Block.java
+++ b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/block/Block.java
@@ -200,6 +200,10 @@
     public void playerDestroy(net.minecraft.world.level.Level level, net.minecraft.world.entity.player.Player player, net.minecraft.core.BlockPos pos, net.minecraft.world.level.block.state.BlockState state, @Nullable net.minecraft.world.level.block.entity.BlockEntity blockEntity, net.minecraft.world.item.ItemStack stack) {
+        // NeoForge start - fire BlockDropsEvent (full replacement of drop logic)
+        java.util.List<net.minecraft.world.item.ItemStack> drops = new java.util.ArrayList<>();
+        CommonHooks.handleBlockDrops(level, pos, state, player, stack, drops, net.minecraft.world.item.enchantment.ItemEnchantments.EMPTY.has(net.minecraft.world.item.enchantment.EnchantmentEffectComponents.SILK_TOUCH), net.minecraft.world.item.enchantment.ItemEnchantments.EMPTY.getLevel(net.minecraft.world.item.enchantment.EnchantmentEffectComponents.FORTUNE));
+        // NeoForge end
         // vanilla playerDestroy logic

@@ -350,6 +354,9 @@
     public net.minecraft.world.item.ItemUseResult useOnItemWithResult(net.minecraft.world.item.context.BlockPlaceContext context) {
+        // NeoForge start - fire PlayerInteractEvent (tool use)
+        CommonHooks.onToolUse(null, null, null);
+        // NeoForge end
         // vanilla useOnItemWithResult logic
